33333>(7/29/02 9:06:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=290.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://doug.feldmann.com/Sigurd.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are pets really a viable raiding tool?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Erm... Emp and VT aren't the only things to raid any more. Just because 2% of the guilds are uber and maybe one or two per server are doing those encounters doesn't mean it's a yardstick for everyone else.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This was really close to the point I was trying to make.  It looks as if you're basing your claims about being mod rod ho's on a fairly narrow range of raids.  I'm not in a teir 1 or 2 guild, but I've found that I can use pets when it matters.  A lot of times, it really doesn't matter and pets are dangerous..   If you're farming halls of testing with a big raid then yeah, get /pet hold or summon a new pet every damn fight.  But when we killed Dozekar I used a pet.  When we killed the other HoT names I used a pet if I wanted to.  For the rest of the raid I made rods, debuffed, and nuked.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  At 55 in ToV, even with Tash and Malo I have a difficult time landing Fire nukes on the cold AoE mobs (for the most part I can hit the non-AoE mobs fine), and I have nothing that hits the Firey Guardians at all. Basically I can burn half my mana trying to get a nuke to stick, or I can make sure all the Clerics stay at FM so we can chain pull.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I'm sorry, but a level 55 mage will be less powerful than a level 60 mage.  It is a very unfair comparison to make.  If you look at all the other level 55 people on your raid, what do you see them doing well?  A level 55 warrior has defensive, but probably will have tons of trouble holding aggro and he'll get decimated by the stronger AEs, and you can only use defensive so often.  A level 55 wizard won't have quite as bad resist issues, as they have fire/cold/magic nukes, but he'll still get resisted a lot or he'll have to waste mana and time using Lures.  A 55 wiz will also get hurt by AEs.  So you can't nuke like a wizzy, but you're not supposed to and quite often rods make a huge difference in how fast you can pull HoT.  <br>
<br>
A 55 rogue/monk/ranger/shadowknight/paladin will be loaded down with bad resist gear(like elemental blankets) and will require lots of healing during every AE fight.  When you summon resist stuff at the start of the raid, pay attention to the people who are asking for stuff..  I bet it you'll only rarely get requests from level 60s.  This is really a big deal..  If you've ever played a healer or watched them during HoT raids, the groups with the lower level people in them tend to require far more healing than the groups with the level 60s.  Heck, you should be able to see that as a mage making rods.  After a big AE fight, which healers need mana the most?  I'm willing to bet it's the clerics with the pre-60 melees.<br>
<br>
A level 55 enchanter does what?  If your guild is really hurting for chanters he might have to do clarity/haste and tash.  I don't know that I would want to rely on a level 55 slower for HoT unless the rest of my force was really uber.  After that, chanters are almost worse off than mages even.  The only cool stackable thing they get other than nukes is Sieve, which is important but not much more important than rods, and a 55 enc will have the same resist issues you do.<br>
<br>
A level 55 druid?  Nuking.. same deal except that they can use cold instead of magic on the fiery guardians.  Healing?  Yeah it's useful for a caster group.  Chloroblast will be a bit risky for a melee group.<br>
<br>
I think you get the idea..<br>
<br>
At level 55 you should feel honored to be able to even be in the Halls of Testing, and don't expect to get the most exciting job there is.  Expect your nukes to get resisted(though they won't be 100%).  Expect your pet to be worthless(Though it won't always be).  Expect to make a lot of rods(But find the time to nuke if you can).  Be happy that you're even there.  If you aren't having fun in HoT at level 55, maybe you'd be better off raiding Kael/Hate or levelling up.<br>
