<br>
For reasons known only to Solusek Ro, our pets would agro every time I mob would AoE, regardless of whether they were behind a corner or not.  The pet owners were safely around a corner, and didn't get a resist messge, let alone get damage.  The pets were right beside their owners and didn't seem to take damage, but would agro without fail.<br>
<br>
We did the best we could to back the pets off before they could get an attack in (if assist hadn't been called) and back them off on enrage.  My pet didn't hit a single mob before assist, the other pets jumped the gun a couple of times, but no where close to every fight.  After 45 minutes we were all ordered to lose our pets.  The MA said they were screwing up mob positioning =(<br>
<br>
After that I just used RoZ on the non-AoE mobs.  /sigh<br>
<br>
It's really f*cked up of VI to require a lvl 60 AA just to be able to use pets.<br>
<br>
P.S.  My Voc: Air pet took little to no damage from anything other than fire AoE mobs, on those it lost maybe 35-50% of HP during the duration of the fight.  Most times it's regen was sufficient to heal it before the next pull.  My buffed MR/FR/CR was something like 179/219/194 (w/o Bard songs).<br>
<br>
P.P.S. (I just reread the thread) I can actually resist most of the AoEs with my resist gear on + CoS + Resist Cold.  If we have a Bard than that's even better.  Also, I can land nukes on just about anything <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  other</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> than the fire mobs and the highest lvl cold mobs. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uusrbinperldashw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>usrbinperl dashw</A> at: 8/1/02 8:42:42 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=290.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=290.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=290.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=290.topic&index=24><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.threadControl?topicID=290.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=290.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=290.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=